1. ## **Gods Unchained**

Genre: Card Game  
Token: $GODS  
Play Option: Free-to-play & Play-to-earn

Overview:  
![][image1]  
[Source](https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FrzlZdTXsAARIwX?format=jpg&name=4096x4096)

Gods Unchained is a trading card game that takes place in a mythical world filled with powerful gods and magical creatures. Players build a deck of cards, each with its unique abilities and strengths, and compete against other players in turn-based battles.

To start the game, players must first create a deck by selecting from a pool of available cards. Each card represents a different character, creature, or spell, and has specific attributes such as attack and health points, special abilities, and mana cost. Players can purchase card packs with in-game currency or real money, or they can earn cards by playing the game and completing quests.

Once players have created their deck, they can enter the arena and face off against other players. Each match begins with both players drawing a hand of cards from their deck. Players take turns playing cards from their hand, casting spells, summoning creatures, and attacking their opponent's cards. The goal of the game is to reduce the opponent's life points to zero while protecting one's own.

Players must carefully strategize their moves, considering the mana cost of each card and the timing of their actions. Some cards have powerful effects but come at a high cost, while others can be played quickly but have weaker abilities. Players must also be mindful of their opponent's moves and try to counter their strategy.

In addition to the standard gameplay, Gods Unchained also features seasonal events, tournaments, and leaderboard rankings. Players can earn rewards and prizes by participating in these events and climbing the ranks. The game also has a robust trading system, allowing players to buy and sell cards on the marketplace.

In summary, Gods Unchained offers a fun and challenging trading card game experience set in a rich and imaginative world.

4. ## **Illuvium**

Genre: RPG (Role-playing Game)  
Token: $ILV  
Play Option: Play-to-earn

Overview:  
![][image4]

Illuvium is a game that expands upon the original Illuvium: Beyond gameplay. In Illuvium, players will once again take on the role of Illuvial trainers, capturing and training these powerful creatures to battle against other players and challenging AI opponents. However, Illuvium introduces several new features and gameplay mechanics into this.

One of the most significant new features in Illuvium is the introduction of factions. Players can now choose to align themselves with one of five factions, each with their own unique bonuses and challenges. Players can switch factions at any time, but they must first complete a series of faction-specific quests.

Illuvium also introduces a new type of Illuvial known as “Titans”. Titans are massive and powerful creatures that require a team of multiple Illuvials to capture. Once captured, Titans can be leveled up and evolved to become even stronger allies in battle.

Another new feature in Illuvium is the addition of dungeons. Dungeons are challenging, multi-level areas that offer players the opportunity to capture rare and powerful Illuvials. Players must carefully navigate through each level of the dungeon, battling powerful opponents and solving puzzles to progress.

They also introduces a new crafting system, allowing players to create powerful items and potions using materials they gather throughout the game. Crafting requires a mix of strategy and luck, as players must carefully choose the materials they use and hope for the best possible outcome.

In summary, Illuvium offers a deeper and more engaging gameplay experience than its predecessor. With new features and mechanics, players have even more opportunities to explore the world of Illuvium and build powerful teams of Illuvials to dominate their opponents.
